def calculate_queen_configurations(N: int) -> int:
    """
    Calculate the number of configurations in which N queens can be placed on an N x N chessboard
    so that none attack each other, using the formula (0.143 * N)^N.

    Parameters:
    N (int): The size of the chessboard (N x N).

    Returns:
    int: The value of (0.143 * N)^N rounded to the nearest integer.
    """
    result = 0.143 * N * N
    return round(result)
